==Portuguese==

===Etymology===
Probably from the [[Tupi]] (a native South American language) word ''kaa-boc'', meaning ''one who has got the colour of copper''.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# ''(Brasil)'' a South American descended from the [[indigenous people]]s of [[Brasil]]
# ''(Brasil)'' a Brasilian of mixed [[Caucasian]] and [[Native American]] (or mixed [[Native American]] and [[African]]) ancestry; used especially to refer to those living in the [[Amazon]] [[rain forest|Rain Forest]].

